Key Match Events: Spencer Strider allowed one run and four hits in seven innings with nine strikeouts, achieving his MLB-best total to 259 and giving the bullpen rest.
Post-Match Reflections: Ronald Acuña Jr. raised both arms and signaled with his hands to the Phillies fans, responding to their boos.
Manager Brian Snitker stated, 'Now the real party starts.'
Braves' Kirby Yates said, 'So far, it’s the best part about being a baseball player.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Braves clinched their sixth straight NL East title, beating the Philadelphia Phillies 4-1.
The game ended with Kirby Yates striking out Brandon Marsh to secure the win.
The Braves celebrated their division title in the locker room with champagne, cigars, and dancing.
